	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f9944473345221><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=11&mid=9944473345221>RE: My first post</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=11&mid=9944473345221#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=46723><span id=Scholar>gdnom</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>62 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Jul 6th 3:22 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.23]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>A wizard is weak by design.&nbsp;&nbsp;Weak all the way until 50.<br><br>The class was designed to frustrate you and make you give up.  They level slow because nobody will want to group with you... unless you have friends.<br><br>Until level 50.. you are crap.  You will get alot of resists.<br><br>Verant designed the wizard to be so frustrating because they don't want to many of them running around.<br><br>But here are your rewards once you reach your 50's.<br>All kinds of Teleports.  M A K E  M O N E Y ! !<br>Best Nukes in the game.<br>You will still have a hard time in pick up groups... but when a raid goes down.. you will be one of the first to be sought out (after cleric and chanter or course).<br><br>Anyways... I hope this gives you an idea of what an everquest wizard is.  I recommend playing a Druid if you don't enjoy challenges.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
