	   <tr><td colspan=2>I am currently playing on the pvp diety test server and will be playing sullon zek.&nbsp;&nbsp;I think that erudites are probable on of the better wizzard races to go because when you put the max of 25 points into intel at the start it puts you up to 142 int which means valuable mana later on.  the other 5 points can go into str to make it so you can carry a bit more weight and not be encumbered so easily.  Playing  a wizard I have no problem soloing monsters as long as i get root off because a wizzies damage spells can do so much damage before root wears off.  If you need to in combat you can cast root again and cast some more nukes.  Another tactic is root, dot, dd(until dot wears off),  then dot, root and dd until it is dead if not already.  Other casters know the true power of a wizzie becuase you will never see a mage, necro, or enchanter follow you trhough a zone to kill you even if you have low hp.  They know they cant so sh*t with no pet because they have low hp and it takes no time at all for a wizzy to deal that damage.  I have had many casters try to pk me but will never follow me through because they risk fighting with no pet and getting their @ss kicked.  A wizzy can also kill a warrior when played right because, unlike casters, thjey have a limited ranged weapon attack and i lvl 16 wizzy can hit up a lvl 16 warrior for most of his hp before the warrior gets a chance to melee.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
